        <heading>2821.  Partnership constituted for term; withdrawal</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2821.  Partnership constituted for term; withdrawal.
If a partnership has been constituted for a term, a partner may withdraw without the consent of his partners prior to the expiration of the term provided he has just cause arising out of the failure of another partner to perform an obligation.</p>
        </content>
